	<dd><a name="comment_2776" ></a>
	<p><em><strong>Max</strong> replies:</em> And of course there will be people in prison between elections who won't be affected.<br />The irony is that if those incarcerated were to be given the vote they would probably vote for a different incarceration--that of capitalism.<br />Capitalism is like a prison, except no-one has noticed the door isn't locked, so you can leave any time. The door in this case being the vote. Use it to bring about a better world without politicians, leaders and the rest of the paraphernalia associated with the exploitative property society that is capitalism.</p>
	<small>
	written 3rd May 2005 <!-- | <a
